                        },
                        "displayName": "Christian Cordova",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "As a humble opinion (and as a user), i do would prefer \"is_nan()\" always returns True or False as the base R and numpy does. If someone wants to check for the input data always can use \"is_null()\" and combine operations to get what they want.",
