                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13381960/comment/17461669",
                    "id": "17461669",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=icook",
                        "name": "icook",
                        "key": "icook",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=icook&avatarId=29388",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=icook&avatarId=29388",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=icook&avatarId=29388",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=icook&avatarId=29388"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Ian Cook",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/New_York"
                    },
                    "body": "As seen in the first link Dewey shared above, the R bindings currently translate the R expression\r\n{code:java}\r\nis.nan(x){code}\r\nto the Arrow expression\u00a0\r\n{code:java}\r\nand_kleene(is_nan(x), is_valid(x)){code}\r\nwhen {{x}} has a floating point data type. This is for consistency with the behavior of R.\r\n\r\nThe gist of this Jira is that we would like to simplify that translation (and other bindings' translations) so they can simply call {{is_nan}} with an option.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=icook",
                        "name": "icook",
                        "key": "icook",
                        "avatarUrls": {
